  "unmapped_findings": [
    "Work hardening behavior exhibits three-stage characteristics: stage 1 (work hardening rate decreases rapidly, related to ferrite deformation), stage 2 (work hardening rate slightly decreases or increases, related to TRIP effect), stage 3 (work hardening rate decreases rapidly, related to deformation localization of ferrite or martensite)",
    "Retained austenite with lower Schmid factor tends to remain untransformed during tensile deformation, while austenite with higher Schmid factor transforms first",
    "Deformation induced martensitic transformation occurs continuously with increasing true strain, transformed martensite acts as barrier for dislocation glide, promotes dislocation accumulation and multiplication",
    "With increasing solution temperature from 700°C to 1000°C, yield strength of specimens decreases gradually, which is attributed to higher austenite volume fraction, microstructure softening and grain coarsening"
  ]
